<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9900] Anticompaction can mix old and new data with DTCS in 2.2+</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9900</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6851&quot; title=&quot;Improve anticompaction after incremental repair&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6851&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6851&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we group sstables before running anticompaction on them to avoid increasing sstable count.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should not do this for DTCS as it can mix new and old data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
